    <abstract id="aspace_ca070de0007732fbf475b7c8635cb367">A letter written by Ernest St. Clair Bijou, a writer and initiator of the Martha Caldwell Bijou Poetry Prize at Wesleyan, to Miss Nancy Ford of <emph render="italic">Brooklyn Life</emph> magazine requesting that the publication review his book of verse, <emph render="italic">Back Woods Sketches</emph>. Bijou refers to himself as "a Brooklyn man." The collection contains one letter and one postcard.</abstract>
